  "title": "chore(jest): update and add linter",
  "body": "Add eslint-jest-linter to have an error if some tests are skipped. \r\n\r\nOther new features are described here: https://facebook.github.io/jest/blog/2017/02/21/jest-19-immersive-watch-mode-test-platform-improvements.html\r\n\r\nI put error, even for \"skipped\" tests. They recommend warn. \r\nWhat's your thoughts about that? \r\n\r\nOne use case I see for the \"warn\" is: if you have a test that is failing for an unknown (or known but hard to fix) reason, and you still want to merge. \r\n\r\n",
